The verbatim "make" program on different OSes varies... to call the same
implementation as the top-level make (e.g. GNU make here for autotools),
normally the $(MAKE) variable should be used.

Part of compile fixes for OpenIndiana support in gloox-1.0.23 as of 2020-02-02

Signed-off: Jim Klimov <jimklimov@gmail.com>

